, leg. D. Erber (
<specimenCount box="[1159,1232,1021,1046]" pageId="10" pageNumber="537" type="male">1 male</specimenCount>
recorded). The song of 
<taxonomicName box="[346,469,1057,1082]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Montana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="537" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barretii">
<emphasis box="[346,469,1057,1082]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="537">M. barretii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other species of this group, because the short verses do not contain microsyllables. Both 
<typeStatus box="[395,454,1094,1118]" pageId="10" pageNumber="537">types</typeStatus>
of verses, short and long, are made from one 
<typeStatus box="[994,1042,1094,1118]" pageId="10" pageNumber="537">type</typeStatus>
of syllables only (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1329,1093,1118]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,887,909]" captionTargetBox="[163,1412,366,861]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,337,866]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Oscillograms of calling songs of Montana species. A— barretii, B— carpetana, C— macedonica, D— stricta. See Table 2 and text for details." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/573665/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="537">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A). Short verses have durations between ca. 100–300 ms, long verses between 1.3–4.5 s.
